## Executive Summary

Epic 4 focuses on building and comparing multiple machine learning models to predict loan approvals. Four different algorithms were trained and evaluated on the preprocessed dataset to identify the best-performing model for deployment. This epic represents the core machine learning phase of the project, where model development, evaluation, and selection occur.

---

## Project Context

Building on the data preprocessing completed in Epic 3, this phase involves:
- Training multiple ML models using the balanced and scaled dataset
- Evaluating each model using comprehensive metrics
- Comparing model performance
- Selecting and saving the best model for deployment in Epic 5

**Input Data:**
- X_train_epic3.csv (features - training set)
- X_test_epic3.csv (features - test set)
- y_train_epic3.csv (target - training set)
- y_test_epic3.csv (target - test set)

**Balanced Dataset:** Loan applications with equal representation of approved and rejected cases

